<item>
            <title>[WFLY-7071] Changing default-realm of Elytron security-domain through CLI can put the server configuration to wrong state</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-7071</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Values of write-attribute operation for default-realm of Elytron security-domain are not checked. It means that CLI allows users to set application server to wrong state. The same happens if realm, which is considered as default-realm, is removed from used security-domain realms. CLI should deny write attribute operation with wrong value (in the same way as it works for another security-domain attributes).&lt;/p&gt;

