                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13290395" author="dlofthouse" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 05:55:18 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=harald.pehl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;harald.pehl&quot;&gt;Harald Pehl&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=claudio4j&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;claudio4j&quot;&gt;Claudio Miranda&lt;/a&gt; In this case the default-realm attribute in the security domain is required to reference one of the referenced security realms, we need some checking in our subsystem to ensure the selected realm is already referenced but as this is slightly outside capabilities and requirements I think worth flagging in case anything else is needed to make it easier to maintain integrity from admin clients.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13290399" author="harald.pehl" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 06:06:19 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed. We should add some kind of client side validation for default-realms of security domains. I filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/HAL-1179&quot; title=&quot;Add validation for default-realm in /subsystem=elytron/security-domain&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HAL-1179&quot;&gt;HAL-1179&lt;/a&gt; to track this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13293087" author="honza889" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2016 05:37:25 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;i think what we need is validation on write attribute  handler - what should be discussed here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13293091" author="dlofthouse" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2016 05:40:06 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 I think a write handler that validates here should be the main thing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
